Module 1¶

Most popular news in recent time¶

  1. This module collects information about most popular news in recent time.
  2. Here, data from 'WION' news channel is collected.
  3. The data consists of recent news topic, duration of video, views, upload date.
  4. From this data, information is collected and analysis is done.
  5. This module is purely based on selenium
  6. In later stage, when i was looking for the documentation i discovered helium which provides the wrapper around selenium

# Converting into single unit
upt=[]
for i in raw_data['Upload_Datetime']:
    lst=i.split('Streamed',1)[-1].strip().split()
    if 'minutes' in lst:
        upt.append(1)
    elif 'minute' in lst:
        upt.append(1)
    elif 'day' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0]))
    elif 'days' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0]))
    elif 'week' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0])*7)
    elif 'weeks' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0])*7)
    elif 'month' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0])*30)
    elif 'months' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0])*30)
    elif 'year' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0])*12*30)
    elif 'years' in lst:
        upt.append(int(lst[0])*12*30) 
    else:
        upt.append(1)
        
raw_data['Days_from_upload']=upt

In [57]:
lem=WordNetLemmatizer()
stop_words=stopwords.words('english')
news_list=list(df['News_Heading'])
tokenized=[nltk.pos_tag(word_tokenize(i)) for i in news_list]
cleaned=[]
unwanted_words=['gravitas','news','exclusive','english','wion','latest','live','reports','world','palki','sharma']
for i in tokenized:
    dummy=[]
    for j in i:
        if j[1].startswith('NN'):
            text=''.join([t for t in j[0] if t.isalpha()])
            if len(text)>2:
                dummy.append(lem.lemmatize(text))
    clean1=[d for d in dummy if d not in stop_words]
    clean2=[c for c in clean1 if c not in string.punctuation]
    clean3=[f.lower() for f in clean2 if f.lower() not in unwanted_words]
    cleaned.append(clean3)

Module 2¶

latest news in recent time & data from 3 channels¶

  1. This module collects information about latest news in recent time.
  2. Here, data from 'WION','BBC News' & 'AL Jazeera' news channel is collected so that the data is not biased.
  3. The data consists of recent news topic, duration of video, views, upload date.
  4. From this data, information is collected and analysis is done.
  5. Controlling the browser and navigating is much easier in helium.
  6. We can also use combination of both.
  7. I prefer selenium for extracting data since i have developed good grip on it while making this project.
  8. And i prefer helium for controlling the browser.
In [34]:
# Initializing driver
print('Initializing driver.....')
driver = start_chrome(maximize=True)
channel_name=['wion','bbc news','Al Jazeera English']
scrapped_text=[]


# Navigate to url 

for c in channel_name:
    print('Navigating to URL.....')
    go_to(('https://www.youtube.com/c/'+c+'/videos'))
    time.sleep(2)

    print(f"Scraping for {c}")
    time.sleep(2)
    h=0
    for i in tqdm(range(50)):
        scroll_down(h)
        time.sleep(1)
        h+=300
    time.sleep(5)
    box=[i.text for i in driver.find_elements_by_id('dismissible')] 
    scrapped_text.append(box)
raw_text=[]
for i in scrapped_text:
    for j in i:
        raw_text.append(j)
print('Scraping done.....raw output file created.')
driver.quit()

lem=WordNetLemmatizer()
stop_words=stopwords.words('english')
news_list=list(df['News_Heading'])
tokenized=[nltk.pos_tag(word_tokenize(i)) for i in news_list]
cleaned=[]
unwanted_words=['gravitas','story','news','exclusive','english','wion','latest','live','reports','world','palki','sharma','bbc','jazeera','newsfeed','stream']
for i in tokenized:
    dummy=[]
    for j in i:
        if j[1].startswith('NN'):
            text=''.join([t for t in j[0] if t.isalpha()])
            if len(text)>2:
                dummy.append(lem.lemmatize(text))
    clean1=[d for d in dummy if d not in stop_words]
    clean2=[c for c in clean1 if c not in string.punctuation]
    clean3=[f.lower() for f in clean2 if f.lower() not in unwanted_words]
    cleaned.append(clean3)

# Function to extract most popular news topics from playlists 

# Initializing driver

print('Initializing driver....')
driver = start_chrome(maximize=True) # Maximize window

# Channel name and youtube url

channel_name='wion'
url='https://www.youtube.com/c/'+channel_name+'/playlists'
print(url)
print('Fetching URL...')

# Loading URL

go_to(url)
time.sleep(2)
print('URL fetched....')

# Setting page height

h=300
print('Scraping phase-1 started...')

# Creating empty list to store data

output_text=[]

# Scrolling upto specified height

for i in tqdm(range(40)):
    scroll_down(h)
    time.sleep(0.2)
    h+=300

# Phase-1
# Extracting the playlist title, video_link and palylist_link

title=[i.text for i in driver.find_elements_by_id('video-title')]
vdo_link=[i.get_attribute('href') for i in driver.find_elements_by_id('video-title')]
playlist_links=[i.get_attribute('href') for i in driver.find_elements_by_xpath("""//*[@id="view-more"]/a""")]
print('Scraping phase 1 successfully completed...')

# Phase-2

print('Scaping phase-2 started....')

# Using loop to get top news title in each playlist
print(f"total {len(playlist_links)} playlists found")
for i in tqdm(playlist_links):
    go_to(i)
    time.sleep(1.5)
    for j in range(10):
        scroll_down(h)
        time.sleep(0.3)
        h+=300
    time.sleep(2)
    vdo_ttl=[t.text for t in driver.find_elements_by_id('video-title')]
    output_text.append(vdo_ttl)
raw_text=[]
for i in output_text:
    for j in i:
        raw_text.append(j)
print('Scraping phase 2 successfully completed....')
print('Scraping done successfully without any error!')

## Cleaning the data

def Clean_text(text):
    text= text.lower()
    text= re.sub(r"cant", "can not", text)
    text= re.sub(r"won't", "will not", text)
    text= re.sub(r"cant", "can not", text)
    text= re.sub(r"wont", "will not", text)
    text= re.sub(r"dont", "do not", text)
    text= re.sub(r"n't", " not", text)
    text= re.sub(r"\'ll", " will", text)
    text= re.sub(r"arent", "are not", text)
    xv=[]
    for i in text.split():
        if i.isalpha()==True:
            xv.append(i)
        elif i.isdigit()==True:
            xc=' '.join(num2words(i).split('-'))
            xv.append(xc)
        else:
            hmm=[]
            for j in i:
                if j.isalpha()==True:
                    hmm.append(j)
                else:
                    hmm.append(' ')
            xv.append(''.join([k for k in hmm]))
    text=' '.join(xv)
    text = re.sub("[^a-zA-Z]", " ", text)
    text = re.sub("\s+", " ", text)
    text=' '.join([i for i in text.split() if i not in stop])
    text=' '.join([i for i in text.split() if i not in unwanted_words ])
    text=' '.join([wnl.lemmatize(i) for i in text.split()])

    return text

def model_result(classifier):
    print('****')
    print(classifier)
    print('****')
    model=classifier
    model.fit(x_train_vec,y_train)
    y_predict=model.predict(x_test_vec)
    y_pred_train=model.predict(x_train_vec)
    print('Test Data Results:')
    print('Mean Absolute Error:', mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_predict))
    print('Mean Squared Error:', mean_squared_error(y_test, y_predict))
    print('Root Mean Squared Error:', np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_predict)))
    print('_________')
    print('Train Data Results:')
    print('Mean Absolute Error:', mean_absolute_error(y_train, y_pred_train))
    print('Mean Squared Error:', mean_squared_error(y_train, y_pred_train))
    print('Root Mean Squared Error:', np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_train, y_pred_train)))
    print('R2 Score:',r2_score(y_train,y_pred_train))

Creating function for sentiment analysis¶










In [41]:



     


def Sentiment_result(inp):
    print('Initializing driver.....')
    url='https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query={}'.format(inp)
    driver = start_chrome(maximize=True)
    print('Navigating to URL.....')
    go_to(url)
    time.sleep(2)
    driver.find_element_by_id("video-title").click()
    time.sleep(2)
    click(Point(200, 300))
    time.sleep(2)
    driver.execute_script('window.scrollTo(0,300);')
    time.sleep(2)
    button=driver.find_element_by_id("icon-label")
    time.sleep(2)
    button.click()
    time.sleep(1)
    sort=driver.find_element_by_xpath("/html/body/ytd-app/div[1]/ytd-page-manager/ytd-watch-flexy/div[5]/div[1]/div/ytd-comments/ytd-item-section-renderer/div[1]/ytd-comments-header-renderer/div[1]/span/yt-sort-filter-sub-menu-renderer/yt-dropdown-menu/tp-yt-paper-menu-button/tp-yt-iron-dropdown/div/div/tp-yt-paper-listbox/a[1]")
    sort.click()
    print('Comments sorted by top comments......')
    print('Loading started........')
    h=0
    for i in tqdm(range(500)):
        scroll_down(h)
        time.sleep(1)
        h+=300
    time.sleep(10)
    print('Scrapping started........')
    com=[i.text for i in driver.find_elements_by_id('content-text')]
    print('Scraping done.....raw output file created.')
    driver.quit()
    data=pd.DataFrame()
    data['Comments']=com
    data['Polarity']=[TextBlob(i).sentiment.polarity for i in data['Comments']]
    def senti(x):
        if x<0:
            return "Negative"
        elif  x ==0:
            return "Neutral"
        else:
            return "positive"
    data['Sentiment'] = data['Polarity'].apply(senti)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    ax=sns.countplot(x='Sentiment',data=data)
    ax.bar_label(ax.containers[0])
    plt.title(f"Movie Name = {inp}")
    plt.show()
